// SPEC §6.13 — `<name debounced=Nms> = expr` is the canonical state-decl
// reactivity attribute form for debounced reactive state. The pre-v0.next
// `@debounced(N) name = expr` keyword-form was retired at S79 (deep-dive
// `scrml-support/docs/deep-dives/debounce-and-timing-2026-05-10.md` §6
// Approach B clean-cut).
//
// This fixture exercises the canonical form on a Shape 1 plain reactive cell.
// Writes to @query are coalesced into a single trailing write 300ms after the
// most recent write request; subscribers fire on the debounced schedule.
<query debounced=300ms> = ""
<input bind:value=@query/>
<p>${@query}</>
